<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:25AM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Calhoun, southwestern Wirt, northwestern Roane and east central
Jackson Counties through 500 AM EDT...
At 425 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Spencer, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Spencer, Reedy, Lucille, Leroy, Peewee and Gay.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
